claim.claim-text:
1. An integrated circuit comprising:
a semiconductor substrate;
a gate dielectric on the semiconductor substrate;
a gate on the gate dielectric;
at least one salicide layer on the semiconductor substrate adjacent the gate and the gate dielectric, the salicide layer incorporating a substantially uniformly distributed and concentrated dopant therein;
an amorphous layer in the surface of the semiconductor substrate beneath the salicide layer and adjacent the gate and the gate dielectric;
a shallow source/drain junction beneath the salicide layer, the shallow source/drain junction being formed in the amorphous layer;
an interlayer dielectric above the semiconductor substrate; and
a contact in the interlayer dielectric to the salicide layer.

3. An integrated circuit comprising:
a semiconductor substrate;
a gate dielectric on the semiconductor substrate;
a gate on the gate dielectric;
an amorphous layer in the surface of the semiconductor substrate adjacent the gate and the gate dielectric;
at least one salicide layer on the semiconductor substrate adjacent the gate and the gate dielectric and over the amorphous layer;
a shallow source/drain junction in the amorphous layer beneath the salicide layer;
an interlayer dielectric above the semiconductor substrate; and
a contact in the interlayer dielectric to the salicide layer.

5. An integrated circuit comprising:
a semiconductor substrate;
a gate dielectric on the semiconductor substrate;
a gate on the gate dielectric;
an amorphous layer in the surface of the semiconductor substrate adjacent the gate and the gate dielectric;
at least one salicide layer on the semiconductor substrate adjacent the gate and the gate dielectric and over the amorphous layer, the salicide layer incorporating a substantially uniformiy distributed and concentrated dopant therein;
a shallow source/drain junction in the amorphous layer beneath the salicide layer;
an interlayer dielectric above the semiconductor substrate; and
a contact in the interlayer dielectric to the salicide layer, the contact being at least one material selected from tantalum, titanium, tungsten, copper, gold, silver, an alloy thereof, a compound thereof, and a combination thereof.
